# Method-level authorization with PreAuthorize

Use @PreAuthorize for application/API-level permission checks.

Allowed usage:
- REST controllers
- application services
- command handlers
- sensitive query services

Use @PreAuthorize for:
- role/authority checks
- workspace-scoped access checks
- marketplace-account-scoped access checks
- manual approval / execution / credential / policy management permissions

Do not use @PreAuthorize:
- in domain layer
- in entities
- in repositories as the main authorization mechanism
- for complex business logic
- with long unreadable SpEL expressions

Prefer:
- simple hasAuthority / hasRole checks
- short calls to a dedicated authorization service bean
- explicit permission names
- business invariants enforced separately inside the use case

Method security does not replace HttpSecurity rules.
Unannotated methods are not automatically protected.
